  "name": "EEG-DaSh",
  "alternateName": "EEGDash",
  "description": "An open-access Python library and catalog that makes 700+ MEEG (EEG, MEG, iEEG, fNIRS, EMG) datasets immediately usable for machine learning. Aggregates recordings from OpenNeuro, NEMAR, Zenodo, Figshare, SciDB, OSF, DataRN, and EEGManyLabs behind a single searchable catalog and a uniform EEGDashDataset interface compatible with MNE-Python, braindecode, and PyTorch. Features automated BIDS repair, PyTorch-native data access, 44 feature extractors across six categories, and HED event annotations for cross-study aggregation.",
